{"title_page": "Government Medical College, Shivpuri", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n|name = Government Medical College, Shivpuri\n|type = Government\n|city =  Shivpuri\n|country = India\n|dean = Dr. Ela Gujariya\n|affiliations = [[Madhya Pradesh Ayurvigyan Vishwavidyalaya]], [[Jabalpur]]\n|website = {{URL|http://www.shivpurimedicalcollege.com}}\n|logo = Shivpuri_medical_college_logo.jpeg\n}}\n\n'''Government Medical College''' in [[Shivpuri]], [[Madhya Pradesh]] is the seventh medical college in the province proposed to be started by the department of medical education, [[Government of Madhya Pradesh]]. This is due to an acute shortage of medical doctors in rural [[Madhya Pradesh]] <ref>{{cite web|title= Shortage of doctors plagues rural health in Madhya Pradesh |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bhopal/shortage-of-doctors-plagues-rural-health/story-izj5rcybiK2q2zWGLslTwK.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= Doctor\u2019s shortage in Government hospitals affecting medical services|url=http://www.thehitavada.com/Encyc/2017/7/18/Doctor-s-shortage-in-Government-hospitals-affecting-medical-services.aspx}}</ref>\n\n==Location==\n[[Shivpuri]] is in the [[Gwalior division]] of northwest [[Madhya Pradesh]]. It is 121&nbsp;km from the city of [[Gwalior]].  The medical college is situated on the [[Agra Bombay Highway]].\n\n==Admission==\nThe college has an annual intake of 100 candidates for M.B., B.S. (Bachelor's degree in Medicine and Surgery).\n\n==Departments==\n*[[Anatomy]]\n*[[Physiology]]\n*[[Biochemistry]]\n*[[Pharmacology]]\n*[[Pathology]]\n*[[Microbiology]]\n*[[Forensic Medicine]]\n*[[Community Medicine]]\n*[[Ophthalmology]]\n*[[Otolaryngology]]\n*[[Medicine]]\n*[[Surgery]]\n*[[Obstetrics & Gynecology]]\n*[[Pediatrics]]\n*[[Anesthesiology]]\n*[[Radiology]]\n*[[Dermatology]]\n*[[Orthopedics]]\n*[[Psychiatry]]\n\n==Affiliation==\nThe medical college is affiliated  to Madhya Pradesh Medical Science University, Jabalpur <ref>{{citenews|title= Madhya Pradesh Medical Science University, Jabalpur|url=http://www.mpmsu.edu.in/}}</ref> and is attached to District Hospital, [[Shivpuri]]  <ref>{{citenews|title= District Administration, Shivpuri|url=http://www.shivpuri.nic.in/health.html}}</ref>\n\n==Inauguration==\n[[Jyotiraditya Scindia]],Member of Parliament, officially inaugurated the [[Government Medical College, Shivpuri]] on 5 March 2019.  Dr. Professor [[Jyoti Bindal]] is the first Dean of this Medical Institute.<ref>{{citenews|title= Govt. Medical College inaugurated in Shivpuri|url=https://www.dailypioneer.com/2019/state-editions/govt-medical-college-inaugurated-in-shivpuri.html}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official Website|http://www.shivpurimedicalcollege.com}}\n\n{{Colleges affiliated to Madhya Pradesh Medical Science University}}\n{{coord missing|Madhya Pradesh}}\n\n[[Category:Medical colleges in Madhya Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Shivpuri]]\n\n==GMC Shahdol==\n1.after Gmc shahdol its Infrastructure is best.\n\n2.http://gmcshahdol.org/\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox university\n|name = Government Medical College, Shivpuri\n|type = Government\n|city =  Shivpuri\n|country = India\n|dean = Dr. Ela Gujariya\n|affiliations = [[Madhya Pradesh Ayurvigyan Vishwavidyalaya]], [[Jabalpur]]\n|website = {{URL|http://www.shivpurimedicalcollege.com}}\n|logo = Shivpuri_medical_college_logo.jpeg\n}}\n\n'''Government Medical College''' in [[Shivpuri]], [[Madhya Pradesh]] is the seventh medical college in the province proposed to be started by the department of medical education, [[Government of Madhya Pradesh]]. This is due to an acute shortage of medical doctors in rural [[Madhya Pradesh]] <ref>{{cite web|title= Shortage of doctors plagues rural health in Madhya Pradesh |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bhopal/shortage-of-doctors-plagues-rural-health/story-izj5rcybiK2q2zWGLslTwK.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= Doctor\u2019s shortage in Government hospitals affecting medical services|url=http://www.thehitavada.com/Encyc/2017/7/18/Doctor-s-shortage-in-Government-hospitals-affecting-medical-services.aspx}}</ref>\n\n==Location==\n[[Shivpuri]] is in the [[Gwalior division]] of northwest [[Madhya Pradesh]]. It is 121&nbsp;km from the city of [[Gwalior]].  The medical college is situated on the [[Agra Bombay Highway]].\n\n==Admission==\nThe college has an annual intake of 100 candidates for M.B., B.S. (Bachelor's degree in Medicine and Surgery).\n\n==Departments==\n*[[Anatomy]]\n*[[Physiology]]\n*[[Biochemistry]]\n*[[Pharmacology]]\n*[[Pathology]]\n*[[Microbiology]]\n*[[Forensic Medicine]]\n*[[Community Medicine]]\n*[[Ophthalmology]]\n*[[Otolaryngology]]\n*[[Medicine]]\n*[[Surgery]]\n*[[Obstetrics & Gynecology]]\n*[[Pediatrics]]\n*[[Anesthesiology]]\n*[[Radiology]]\n*[[Dermatology]]\n*[[Orthopedics]]\n*[[Psychiatry]]\n\n==Affiliation==\nThe medical college is affiliated  to Madhya Pradesh Medical Science University, Jabalpur <ref>{{citenews|title= Madhya Pradesh Medical Science University, Jabalpur|url=http://www.mpmsu.edu.in/}}</ref> and is attached to District Hospital, [[Shivpuri]]  <ref>{{citenews|title= District Administration, Shivpuri|url=http://www.shivpuri.nic.in/health.html}}</ref>\n\n==Inauguration==\n[[Jyotiraditya Scindia]],Member of Parliament, officially inaugurated the [[Government Medical College, Shivpuri]] on 5 March 2019.  Dr. Professor [[Jyoti Bindal]] is the first Dean of this Medical Institute.<ref>{{citenews|title= Govt. Medical College inaugurated in Shivpuri|url=https://www.dailypioneer.com/2019/state-editions/govt-medical-college-inaugurated-in-shivpuri.html}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official Website|http://www.shivpurimedicalcollege.com}}\n\n{{Colleges affiliated to Madhya Pradesh Medical Science University}}\n{{coord missing|Madhya Pradesh}}\n\n[[Category:Medical colleges in Madhya Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Shivpuri]]\n", "name_user": "Khushal Parihar", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia